    "B. Task-Agnostic Graph CondensationThe optimization strategies currently employed in GC are specifically designed for the classification task, heavily relying on class labels.",
    "However, the entanglement of the GC optimization process with task-related labels can potentially hinder performance in other downstream tasks.",
    "The recent study, CTGC [113], investigates self-supervised learning to enhance the task adaptability of GC for link prediction, and clustering tasks.",
    "This confirms the feasibility of extending GC to a wider spectrum of practical scenarios and delineates promising directions for future research, including anomaly detection [114], graph reconstruction [115], and graph generation [116].",
    "C. Efficient Evaluation for Condensed GraphsIn the realm of GC, the primary objective is to create high-quality condensed graphs."
